The Chairman, Tincan Island Chapter of the Association of Nigerian Licensed Customs Agents (ANLCA), Peter Akintoye Ojo has averred that the Association would use every constitutional means to recover all its property in wrong hands. Ojo, in a new year message to his members urged them to be law abiding in their dealings and ensure they carry out their duties with due diligence. The Customs broker, who was reacting to an interview that he was not the authentic chairman of the chapter, averred that he was duly elected and not selected to occupy the office. N50bn NIMASA Floating Dock To Become Operational In First… ANLCA Laments 30,000 Job Losses To Border Closure,… “ I Peter Akintoye Ojo, the State Chairman, Apapa Chapter of Association of Nigerian Licensed Customs Agents (ANLCA), elected under NECON headed by Hon. Tony Iju Nwabunike, the current National President of ANLCA. “We fel it is necessary to address our people as the year begins 2022. We wish them happy New Year and pray that this year will bring success and greatness to us all. “Having said that, we thank God so far for where we are coming from and where we are going regarding the operations. I am happy we have been able to address and resolve a lot of issues, even though we still have some unresolved ones. “As you know particularly with this present government. It is the government that believes in the rule of law. That is why we are following all matters according to the rule of the law, believing that dialogue with other stakeholders will make things better. Reacting to allegation of Mojeed, Ojo said: “Initially, I did not want to react to that. I believe in the adage that silence is the best answer to such. However, since you have asked the question, I will answer you.